HEADWORD: Phytolacca
<hw>Phy`to*lac"ca</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>fyto`n</grk> plant + It. <ets>lacca</ets> lac.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of herbaceous plants, some of them having
berries which abound in intensely red juice; poke, or
pokeweed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phytolite</ent>⟦br⟧
